neuronResources.note: All reconstructions from this paper are enhanced multi-signal swc (eswc) files. The original image stacks had two channels: Red for Microtubule and Green for F-actin. The multi-signal information (with four columns, two each for microtubule and F-actin) is at the bottom half of the source file,  after the 7 column swc neuron tree (after the tag #CHANNELSWC at the middle of the eswc file). For each signal, the first column indicates fraction of volume occupied and the second column indicates average intensity. Signal information and the neuron tree have the same number of rows.
